    "recap_headline": "St. John's University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "CHARLOTTE, N.C.\n\u2013 The St. John's baseball team fell in the series finale at Charlotte in a 10-9 decision on Sunday afternoon.\nThe Red Storm (7-12) led by as many as three runs on two separate occasions and scored the go-ahead run in the ninth inning, but the 49ers (13-6) walked it off in the bottom of the ninth to avoid the series sweep.\nThe top third of the Johnnies' offense carried the load, with\nJon LeGrande\n,\nJayder Raifstanger\nand\nShaun McMillan\nall collecting two hits apiece and each driving in at least one run.\nLewis Rodriguez\nwas a perfect 3-for-3 from the dish, adding a run and an RBI to his line.\nJack Tate\ncame in to pinch hit in the top of the ninth and delivered an RBI double to put St. John's ahead at the time.\nAdam Agresti\nreached base four times, all via walks, including two intentional passes.\nThe pitching staff was led by\nIan Mowad\n, who went 3.2 innings to start. Four relievers came in and recorded outs, with\nVictor Frederick\nand\nTyler Longoria\nas the only two pitchers out of the bullpen to go longer than 1.0 inning.\nAfter a scoreless first inning, St. John's got on the board first with a four-run inning. Following a pair of walks from Agresti and\nDylan Fitzsimmons\n, an\nAyden Frey\nsingle scored Agresti with runners on first and second and no outs. Three sacrifice bunts kept the line moving, as the Johnnies capitalized on an error, extending the lead to 3-0. LeGrande knocked in the final run of the inning to make it 4-0.\nCharlotte answered with two runs in the bottom of the frame to make it 4-2.\nIn the top of the fourth frame, the Johnnies added an insurance run. With\nSean Britt\nreaching on an error and Rodriguez singling, the Red Storm had two runners on with no outs. Britt advanced to third after LeGrande grounded into a double play. Raifstanger roped a single to center to bring Britt around to score, 5-2.\nThe 49ers chipped away at the lead with a pair of tallies to make it 5-4.\nThe Johnnie offense kept rolling in the top of the fifth, using a two-out rally to take their second three-run advantage of the afternoon. With two outs and runners on first and second, LeGrande singled to drive in his second run of the contest. Following a Raifstanger walk, McMillan delivered an RBI single to plate the second run of the inning and make it 7-3.\nCharlotte erased the deficit in the bottom of the sixth and took the lead in the seventh, 8-7.\nSt. John's mounted a comeback of its own in the top of the ninth inning. Rodriguez used a one-out single to start the rally and stole second before LeGrande moved him over to third.\nDown to their final out, the Johnnies tied the contest with an RBI single from Raifstanger. In the next at-bat,\nJack Tate\nscored Raifstanger from first on a pinch-hit double to give St. John's a 9-8 lead.\nThe 49ers sealed the deal in the bottom of the ninth to avoid the series sweep, 10-9.\nSt. John's is back in action on Tuesday at Stony Brook to continue its seven-game road trip. First pitch from Joe Nathan Field is set for 3 p.m."
